parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Difficulty turning the key in the ignition
key gets stuck in the ignition

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door locks and latches can cause the doors to become stuck or jammed, leading to safety concerns and potential accidents.
symptoms: Doors become locked and cannot be opened from the inside or outside

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the throttle body/actuator can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate while accelerating, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving on the highway.
symptoms: The "wrench" light on the dashboard illuminates
and the vehicle may go into "limp home mode."

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to slip out of gear, lose power, or hesitate while shifting, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving on the highway.
symptoms: The vehicle slips out of gear
and the vehicle may go into "limp home mode."

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or hesitate while starting, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving on the highway.
symptoms: the ignition switch is difficult to turn
and the vehicle may not start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the neutral safety switch can cause the vehicle to shift into neutral while driving, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving on the highway.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into neutral while driving
and the transmission makes unusual noises.
